COVID-19. The government immediately rolled out its response which limited the impact to less than 300 cases and no deaths. However, GDP fell by close to 9%, a record low in its history.

The COVID response bought time for the government to consult with the public and developed the New National Digital Identity. This requires all adults in Bhutan to have a digital ID by July 2021, from which a blockchain-enabled digital ID can be issued. The government is still figuring out how it would be used. However, we understand there are big plans on leveraging the database when it is developed. We do not see an immediate need for this technology as the government’s aim is to go paperless. In fact, such a digital report would be near useless if all the government agencies rely on paper records. Any decisions can either be requested from officials or sent for approval digitally with stakeholders to simply sign online.

1Q2021 was very hot but cooled down quickly by the 4th week. Over 1Q, LT as measured by the DBSI Index was the only index in the green.

LTPAT and CRTB each constituted 14.6% of the DBSI, the same as LT. LFPAT was one of the worst since January 2019 with a YTD loss of -5.6% vs QTD loss of -1.9%

Meanwhile, TSK EWY TRS and TAO EWY ROW TRS all constituted 10.
